#Text=France , Italy , UK sending military advisers to Libya ; photojournalists killed in Misrata
#Text=Thursday , April 21 , 2011
#Text=La Russa in 2007 .
#Text=Image : G. dallorto .

#Text=France and Italy have announced along with the United Kingdom that they will be sending military advisers to help Libyan rebels in their fight against the forces of Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi .
#Text=Italian Minister for Defence Ignazio La Russa said Wednesday that his country will send ten instructors .
#Text=French officials said they would send fewer than ten .
#Text=The British Foreign Secretary , William Hague , said they would send a team that could possibly contain up to twenty advisers .
#Text=La Russa said in a news conference that the advisers ' roles had yet to be determined , " They wo n't be on the battlefield .

#Text=UN High Commissioner for Human Rights Navi Pillay stated , amidst reports of snipers attacking civilians in many towns , that use of such munitions would  inevitably lead to civilian casualties " , whilst also calling for NATO forces to " exercise the utmost caution and vigilance so as not to kill civilians by mistake " .

column1: #Text=Pillay praised the Libyan government for allowing on Monday a U.N. humanitarian base in the capital city of Tripoli .

#Text=Meanwhile , fighting has continued between rebel and pro-government forces this Wednesday in the besieged western port city of Misrata , where residents are pleading for international intervention .

#Text=British photojournalist Tim Hetherington , who co-directed the documentary film Restrepo , which was nominated for an Academy Award for Best Documentary Feature this year , died from wounds he suffered in an RPG attack in the city .
#Text=In besieged Libyan city of Misrata .
#Text=Indiscriminate shelling by Qaddafi forces .
#Text=No sign of NATO .
#Text=—
#Text=Tim Hetherington 's last tweet
#Text=His colleagues , photographers Chris Hondros and Guy Martin were also severely wounded .

#Text=Hondros suffered a severe brain injury leaving him in a critical condition and eventually succumbed to his injury at a triage center and Martin , a British citizen , was injured by shrapnel , and is now receiving vascular surgery .
#Text=Another with the group , Michael Christopher Brown also received shrapnel wounds which were not life-threatening .
#Text=Hetherington last updated his Twitter account on Tuesday , which read , " In besieged Libyan city of Misrata .
